<br>
1. Ubah_Guild_00* (could be any of them) - Come join our guild we need more clerics. We wil give you your epic, (insert list of current hard to get spells) and such and such other ubah_items. <br>
       Is this what you mean by wait a year till we can do it ourselves? So you guys can poach more players to zerg through zones?<br>
<br>
2. Ubah_Guild_001 Enchanter In need of a shard for VT - He trains us who are holding the camp to try and get rid of us (no chat beforehand) His train dreails on himself and the we  save him. His thanks is to then try and train us again, same result, we  asked him wtf he is doing (insert shard remark here). We say just sit here we see them drop fairly commonly and we dont need them so you can loot it, he then tries to ks us. <br>
       The  fact that a lvl 60 enchanter (pre pop) could not do any of these things succesfully nor mezz the 4 mobs he was training when it went wrong  speaks loudly for the skill of such a guild. When I spoke to a friend in said guild he said this guy has a rep in the guild for that and nothing would be done about it. Enchanters attitude was I need this to go here so you people in a lesser guild  have to leave so I can get what I want. Sounds familiar? <br>
<br>
3. Ubah_Guild_002 - Members (all lvl 60 or near) ksing  people in The Hole and then proceeding to wipe (zerg one could say) every mob they could find so the xp grp there had nothing to kill and thus no xp. When asked in tells their response was we are bored.<br>
        These are the people already in said zones and your worried about us going there? I Talked to an officer in that guild he sorted it but would he if I had not known him for  a fair while? I doubt it from other things said.<br>
<br>
4. Ubah_Guild_003 Paladin - Working on his faction for a zone trains people xping. His statement as gate was casting was &quot;thought you could use these&quot; <br>
        Seeing as  the duo were already engaged in a melee  and this was said in say (very easy to miss with battle spam and after he had trained us) it is very hard to see this as a kind and thoughtful act more of a you are killing mobs I need for faction. You are worried about us training a graveyard?<br>
<br>
5. Ubah_Guild_004 Member - I turn up at a pop camp fully spawned, only one other person in the zone and I know where they hunt pretty much every night and they are not around this camp. I proceed to start killing, after about 15 mins this person turns up and pulls 2 mobs from my camp I go and get one  back and I get tells I am camping these. I reply No you were not in the zone when I arrived and the camp was spawned so obviously you weren't here before me. He replies yes i was  I just went and played another toon for a while but I'm back now. I ask so is this another case of Ubah_Guild_004 wanting a camp so everyone else  has to leave. His response was if you want to see it that way yes.<br>
        Have since sorted this one out with this person and he's a nice guy but the attitude of  I am in Ubah_Guild_00*  you can just piss off was there at the start. Same attitude as Ubah_Guild_001  Enchanter.<br>
<br>
6. Ubah_Guild_005 attempting AD had that many people in the zone no one else could play there because of lag (would that be zerging) <br>
          This is one of the things you guys are saying will happen to you if others gain access to HoH, yet did you guys show courtesy and leave the zone to try again later when so many people not in Ubah_Guild_005 were complaining about the lag? No.  When CB and VoLS attempted AD no such complaints where made.. if they had more people there than you why wasnt the lag worse?<br>
<br>
Do we complain to Ubah_Guildler_00* - I see your posts here that  my guildies dont do that (news for you guys they DO) or if they do tell us we will deal with it.<br>
Why bother see point 2 and point 7.<br>
<br>
7. Ubah_Guild_006 Guildleader Whilst defendng  one of his members as a notorious trainer - Something along the lines of this;<br>
If your not in my guild you obviously cant play your toon and were not worthy  of consideration.<br>
      Whilst it might not be fair to paint all members of a guild because of the actions of one member, the guild leader tarnishing his is another matter when he publicy states such opinions.<br>
<br>
All this being said as a rule my dealings with people in thes guilds on a day to day basis is very good and I have nothing but praise for the majority of the ones I run across but as you can see every guild has some bad apples and just as you dont like to be tarred with the same brush as  the bad apples in you guild we dont want to be tarred with the same brush as  bad apples who arent in YOUR guild let alone if they were in ours.<br>
<br>
That being said the common theme amongst these incidents is my Guild is Ubah and yours isn't so therefore if we want something we should  have it. I also wonder sometimes how proud some of these guys are of their Ubah_Guild_00* status... Pre LoY it was amazing how many of these members where fully anon, sometimes a whole group of them and yes even officers. Either they are ashamed or they had something to hide.<br>
<br>
Easy to see why the same conclusion is jumped to again right ?  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94690"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.dilligaf.com.au/faerar/faerarbanner.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eriadoc>Eriadoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/10/03 10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=177>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> Well, it has been mentioned in many places, but I would like to state that this Rathe &quot;community&quot; that is continually referred to seems to have striking similarities to society class wars.  98% of the people (non-wealthy) are not represented, while the 2% set rules and standards that best serve their own interests.  This &quot;community&quot; has not taken into consideration the smaller guilds, and in most cases, even the mid-sized guilds.<br>
<br>
I will never support PoP flag mobs being on a rotation, nor will I frown upon teaming up to get flagged for higher level planes.  In the end, if two guilds team up to get into a plane, they still have to survive in that plane on their own.  I don't think you will be seeing Far Seekers taking on Solusek Ro anytime soon, but we would do fine in the 3rd tier planes, and possibly higher.  If the elite guilds on this server want exclusive access to certain content, simply go where the lower-tier guilds cannot go yet (Elemental Planes, PoTime).<br>
<br>
This is not intended to be a flame, by any means (I seldom post here, and those who know me would know better).  However, I don't see too many different ways to read this situation, when it's the high-powered guilds making such a fuss over other people experiencing public game content.  If &quot;cockblocking&quot; is the term of choice for many here, I can certainly understand that viewpoint.  I really can't classify the counter argument as anything but elitism.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
