Noble Blade and Spirit of Tunare teamed up on one Avatar of War, one hour before server was coming down, AFTER both of us had already killed it ourselves, several times each.  This was done to prevent loot from being eaten by the patch, and it was made very clear that if BOTS or Tindi wanted Avatar of War, he was all theirs.  You kill Aerin Dar on your own, even once, and I don’t care who you bring to your raid.  Chances are if you could kill Aerin Dar alone, you wouldn’t begin wholesale flagging of people from 35 other guilds.<br>
<br>
As for us forming from two guilds, yes, we were Noble House and Silver Blade.  We were one entity for all rotations and reservations.  We are now one guild, and have been since Dec 5, 2000.  We are still one entity for all rotations.  I practice what I preach.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Again if this is so it's not hard to send your guild a tell and say hey we would like a shot at mob X when he spawns.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The unwritten, backdoor room conventions made up by the big guilds and the smoking man, is that you don’t back to back kill FCFS mobs, especially PoP mobs so that we can all get what we need.  Its made easier by the fact that if a guild has extra flags they don’t need, you can send along a few to get them taken care of.  It’s a really nice system when you’re done with needing flags and another guild has a recently player return from retirement because they hit new content they want to check out.  And as for that tell, you can’t begin to understand how amazingly difficult it is for other guilds to do that.  I guess it’s pride, I dunno, but recently I had a member of a guild try and work out a shot on a rotation mob and that member got chewed out for being civil and asking.<br>
