<br>
Please see above at the countless times the similarities between PoP flag mobs and other rotation mobs have been made.<br>
<br>
1)  Rare spawn (3+ days)<br>
2)  Contested spawn (35 guilds+ looking to kill)<br>
3)  Desireable loot (for ANY non-VT/Ssra guild)<br>
<br>
Just because you can't make the internal connection between the similarities doesn't invalidate the argument.  We are not talking about two guilds teaming up on Orc_Pawn01 who respawns every 10-20 minutes and there are 31 of in the zone, and has been in the game since 3/19/1999.  We are talking about a precedent that could allow 3, 4, 5, guilds to permafarm Aerin Dar for flags and loot until everyone on the Rathe got their HoH flag and they all got their respective desired items.  This would have the increased negative impact that guilds that can and do still want access to Aerin Dar would lose that same access, at which point, the teaming guilds would lose the right to do what they have been doing.  So you're suggesting, that simply because people COULD, but haven't, teamed on Burrower, THO, TIV (all of whom have no keys to any zones, so their relevance to PoP mobs is questionable), we should go on a merry-go-round that winds us right back where we say we should be in the first place:  No guilds teaming on PoP flag mobs, UNLESS they become a formal alliance for all mobs.<br>
